					<div class="commentbody">Is there a way to substituted evaporated milk for the sweetened condensed milk?</div>
					<hr size="1" noshade />
				
					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On January 20, 2006 at 02:31 AM, Michael Chu said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Anonymous wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>Is there a way to substituted evaporated milk for the sweetened condensed milk?</div></div><br />
I haven't done this myself, but I've read that if you bring 1 cup (8 oz. or 235 mL) evaporated milk to a simmer and add 1-1/4 cup (125 g) sugar and stir until the sugar has fully dissolved, it is a good approximate of sweetened condensed milk.</div>
