					<div class="commentheading">On March 11, 2007 at 03:42 AM, guest (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>that's not fudge, it's ganache</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Chocolate softened with cream or milk or soft fat isn't an easy way to make fudge.  It's <i>ganache,</i> a completely different thing.  That's why it's so much easier to get it smooth.<br />
<br />
Try rolling this condensed milk ganache into little balls and coating them in cocoa, spices or chocolate, perhaps with a nut or a piece of candied fruit or ginger in the middle, or hollow them out and inject a liquid center...</div>
