					<div class="commentbody">To make this fudge more diabetic friendly, try this substitution for the sweetened condensed milk.  Note that it isn't sugar free (nor will the fudge be sugar free because of the chips you add)--but it does make it "easier" on the diabetics (like me).<br />
<br />
http://www.recipezaar.com/no-sugar-added-sweetened-condensed-milk-395627<br />
<br />
To synopsize, in a small bowl mix 1/3 cup boiling water + 2 tbls<br />
4 tablespoons butter<br />
3/4 cup Splenda<br />
1 Cup NONFAT dry milk powder (see website for some cautions as some are "thicker" than others)<br />
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract.<br />
<br />
I use this total recipe in place of the 14 oz can of sweetened condensed milk.</div>
