					<div class="commentheading">On May 01, 2010 at 05:21 AM, Stephanie (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Easiesdt way to make this recipe, period</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I'm not sure why no one has mentioned this, and i admit I may have missed it in the comments, but the easiest way to make this fudge is to heat the butter and condensed milk in a microwave safe bowl, for about 2 minutes in the microwave. Then pour it over the chocolate chips and let it sit for about a minute to melt the chocolate, then stir! I've made it twice this way and it has turned out lovely both times. It utilizes the convenience of the microwave while completely eliminating the risk of burning the chocolate.</div>
					<hr size="1" noshade />
				
					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On May 04, 2010 at 01:32 AM, Ngaire (guest) said...</div>
